==English==

===Etymology===
{{Lat}} ''administratus'', past participle of ''administrare.''

===Verb===
'''administrate''' (''[[transitive]]'') ([[administrates]], [[administrated]], [[administrating]])

#to [[administer]]
#{{computing}} the act or function of providing maintenance and general housekeeping for computer systems, networks, peripheral equipment, etc.
#:Example:  The job is to '''administrate''' the network.

